Yes it’s possible to push a JSON file. And yes you would do it like you said, but make sure you give it the full path (so must at least begin with a /):

    http2_push /payload_x.json;

To set out the x variable based on the version query param you should be able to use `$arg_version`:

    http2_push /payload_$arg_version.json;

Not you will still need to request the JSON File from the browser, but then it will pick up the pushes resource rather than requesting it all the way from the servers.

