When you &quot;`new`&quot; something then you need to &quot;`delete`&quot; it. Calling &quot;`delete[]`&quot; on something you called &quot;`new`&quot; on (instead of `new[]`) is undefined behavior.

In your case you called `l=new Rec` in `Pila::push` but then later called `delete [] l;` in `Pila::~Pila`

The most minimal change would be something like

    Pila::~Pila() {
        while(l!=0) {
            auto next = l-&gt;next;
            delete l;
            l = next;
        }
    }

Or you can get `Rec` a proper set of copy and destruction operations, up to you.

